Another thought: reason $mu so confident in calendar Q2 being inventory peak is that’s when both:
*wafer cuts flow thru (Q422 cuts and 6 month processing times); and
*peak demand seasonality (eg Apple starts pulling in bits ahead of iPhone 15 product cycle + Christmas inv build)
DeFi Surfer 🫐,💎: Thinking about $mu earnings, that NAND industry is delaying node transitions reflects (1) how bad this downturn is and (2) how the NAND industry is fairly mature (ie not costdowns or bust).
Also the market will probably be surprised by how much $lrcx memory revenue is down YoY.
